{"type":"message","id":"cc5c0129","parentId":"b74755ee","timestamp":"2026-03-12T02:34:57.511Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to install Skillhub store according to a specific URL. Let me break this down:\n\n1. The user provided a URL: https://skillhub-1388575217.cos.ap-guangzhou.myqcloud.com/install/skillhub.md\n2. They want me to \"安装Skillhub商店\" which translates to \"install Skillhub store\"\n\nThis is a clear instruction to install something from a URL. I should:\n1. First, read the content from that URL to understand what needs to be installed\n2. Then execute the installation instructions\n\nLet me start by fetching that URL to see what the installation instructions are. I can use `curl` or `wget` to retrieve the content.\n\nActually, looking at my available tools, I have `agent-browser` which is a headless browser tool. That might be suitable for fetching web content. But I also have `exec` which can run curl/wget commands.\n\nGiven that this is just fetching a markdown file from a URL, a simple curl command would be sufficient. Let me use `exec` with curl to fetch the content.\n\nI'll:\n1. Use `exec` to curl the URL and get the installation instructions\n2. Then follow those instructions to install Skillhub\n\nLet me proceed.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"我会帮你安装 Skillhub 商店。让我先获取安装说明。"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_ba97fbd8ea8c46188f24034a","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"curl -s https://skillhub-1388575217.cos.ap-guangzhou.myqcloud.com/install/skillhub.md"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"stepfun/step-3.5-flash:free","usage":{"input":11148,"output":625,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":11773,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773282893865}}
